v0.3.2 

Improvement: enforced authentication on all server actions and APIs, mitigation of possible NoSQL injections
Bugfix: Undo of a node deletion did not reset the correct node order
Bugfix: Ctrl+X/Ctrk+V keyboard shortcut did not work for cut/paste

v0.3.1

Feature: Preferred child templates
Feature: XY-chart field type
Improvement: direct template duplication and import from another tree in the Templates page
Improvement: direct tree duplication and in the Roots page
Bugfix: Fix broken github link feature (api.github.com allowed as external content) 
Bugfix: unneeded reload caused uploads to reset add child node forms


v0.3.0

Feature: unlimited Undo/Redo functionality on nodes actions
Improvement: Server-side session management
Improvement: Automatic tree reload applied back to all trees (not only shared ones) since conflicts and potential data losses may arise from working on the same tree on different pcs/tabs.
Improvement: Confirmation form for updating existing node names if the template changes
Improvement: Conditional rules order can be rearranged
Improvement: Add node form: template selection and field edit unified in a single modal form 
Improvement: Large images are scaled to user specified height instead of width, smaller images are not stretched
Bugfix: clones and their descendants are correctly updated everywhere in the tree without need of a tree reload
Bugfix: Double click in the edit node form does not trigger a second edit form window

v0.2.1

Improvement: Polished interface
Improvement: Keyboard navigation
Improvement: Reload tree, with keyboard shortcut 'r', added
Bugfix: automatic tree reload only on changes of another shared user

Known issues:

Undo needs proper command pattern implementation to work well with the database and has been disabled
Descendants of clones are updated only in their first instance until page is refreshed

v0.2
Feat: share read-only trees publicly with a link
Feat: custom logo setting in the admin panel
Improvement: Shared trees are visually identified
Bugfixes
